data.description: You will feel right at home in this stunning stucco and stone two story home nestled in Struthers Ranch. With loads of curb appeal, breathtaking Pikes Peak views, beautiful landscape, and a welcoming covered porch, this home is sure to please! Greeted with plank wood floors and vaulted ceilings that lead you to a formal living room with large windows and natural light, then on to a formal dining area with plenty of space for the whole family. The dreamy gourmet kitchen features loads of cherry cabinets that are accented by the vaulted ceiling with recessed lighting, stainless steel appliances, a center island, and eating nook with a sliding walk-out that perfectly frames the mountains. From here, you can head into the great room and warm up by the gas fireplace surrounded by stacked stone, a tv nook with a shiplap backdrop, and enjoy more of those mountain views. Completing the main level is a charming laundry room with cabinets and a window. Head upstairs where you will find a stunning owners retreat with a coffered ceiling and a barn door that opens to the adjoining 5-piece bath featuring a soaking tub framed by stacked stone, a large window to let natural light in, his and her vanities and a large walk-in closet. Down the hall are two additional good-sized bedrooms and a full bath. Downstairs is a finished basement with a spacious family room or game room with LVP floors, two more spacious bedrooms with large closets and full bath. This level makes a great space for guests. The backyard is a wonderful space to enjoy Colorado, featuring a large stamped concrete patio, new plush grass, and a rock area with a firepit, plus the one of the best views of Pikes Peak and the Front Range in Colorado! Conveniently located near schools, shopping, and easy access to 1-25 for a quick commute to Denver. You won’t want to miss this one!
